================================================================================
Public specifications used as implementation basis
================================================================================

- Hangul Word Processor 5.0 file format specification, revision 1.3
  (Hancom Inc., 2018)
  https://www.hancom.com/support/downloadCenter/hwpOwpml
- KS X 6101 - Open Word-processor Markup Language (OWPML) / HWPX
  Korean Agency for Technology and Standards.
  https://standard.go.kr/

================================================================================
Inspiration and cross-reference (no source code is copied)
================================================================================

- python-hwpx (airmang) — https://github.com/airmang/python-hwpx
  The idea that the <hp:linesegarray> rendering cache must be removed
  after any text edit, and the general "label > direction" path syntax
  for table navigation, were learned from this public implementation.
  python-hwpx is released under a non-commercial license; none of its
  source code is included, redistributed, or linked at runtime in this
  project. All algorithms were re-implemented independently from the
  OWPML specification.

- hwpxlib / hwplib / hwp2hwpx (neolord0, Apache License 2.0)
  https://github.com/neolord0/hwpxlib
  Cross-referenced for OWPML element attribute interpretation.

- Hancom Developer Forum (https://forum.developer.hancom.com)
  Public Q&A, in particular on linesegarray rendering-cache behaviour,
  was referenced for correctness.

